Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the behavior of the distribution of GCV (Generalized Cross-Validation) smoothing parameter estimates near zero. GCV is a probabilistic method used in statistical analysis to estimate the smoothing parameter in non-parametric regression. The paper uses mathematical and statistical analysis to study the behavior of the distribution of GCV estimates near zero. Therefore, this paper belongs to the sub-category of Probabilistic Methods in AI.
